news_header: A 3.5 magnitude earthquake occurred in Lake Vänern, Sweden, causing no injuries but surprising local residents.
news_original_title: Ruotsissa epätavallisen voimakas maanjäristys – ”Aivan kuin suuri kaivuri olisi jyrännyt taloon”
news_text: A 3.5 magnitude earthquake struck Lake Vänern in Sweden, reported by various news outlets. Local authorities confirmed no injuries. Seismologist Björn Lund noted such earthquakes occur every three to five years. The last significant quake was in 2016. Resident Katrin Jedselius described the experience as frightening.
